## TERMS AND CONDITIONS

### 1. DEFINITIONS

"Annual Revenue" means the total gross revenue of a Legal Entity and all
its Affiliates during the most recently completed fiscal year, calculated in
accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP).

"For-Profit Agricultural Enterprise" means any Legal Entity engaged in
commercial seed production, seed sales, crop breeding for profit, agricultural
biotechnology, agrochemicals, or related agribusiness activities, excluding
farmer cooperatives and producer organizations.

"Legal Entity" means the union of the acting entity and all other entities
that control, are controlled by, or are under common control with that entity.
"Control" means (i) the power to direct the affairs of such entity, or (ii)
ownership of fifty percent (50%) or more of the outstanding shares or beneficial
ownership of such entity.

"Licensed Work" means Bijmantra, including all source code, object code,
documentation, configuration files, assets, and associated materials contained
in the official repository and distributions.

"Licensor" means Denish Dholaria and his successors and assigns.

"Managed Service" means making the functionality of the Licensed Work
available to third parties over a computer network as a primary offering,
including but not limited to software-as-a-service (SaaS), platform-as-a-service
(PaaS), infrastructure-as-a-service (IaaS), or any hosted or cloud-based offering
where the Licensed Work is a substantial component.

"Prohibited Technology" means any technology, method, or practice designed to:
- Restrict the use of genetic material (GURTs)
- Produce sterile seeds or prevent seed saving (Terminator Technology)
- Create farmer dependency on proprietary chemicals (Seed Dependency Technology)
- Prevent farmers from saving, replanting, or sharing seeds
See Section 4.1 for detailed definitions and exemptions.

"You" (or "Your") means the individual or Legal Entity exercising
permissions granted by this License.

