### 3. ADDITIONAL USE GRANT

You may use the Licensed Work for any purpose, including production use and
commercial use, EXCEPT for Excluded Purposes.

#### 3.1 EXCLUDED PURPOSES

The following are Excluded Purposes and require a separate Commercial License:

(a) MANAGED SERVICE RESTRICTION
You may NOT offer the Licensed Work to third parties as a Managed Service without
a Commercial License, UNLESS you are:
- A For-Profit Agricultural Enterprise with Annual Revenue < $1,000,000 USD
- A government agency or publicly-funded breeding program
- A CGIAR center or affiliated program
- A registered non-profit organization or NGO
- An educational institution (subject to institutional licensing in Section 3.2.1)
- A farmer cooperative or producer organization

(b) PROHIBITED TECHNOLOGY RESTRICTION
ALL users (regardless of revenue) are prohibited from using the Licensed Work
in connection with any Prohibited Technology. See Section 4 for details.

#### 3.2 EXEMPTIONS AND GEOGRAPHIC TIERS

The following organizations are EXEMPT from the $1,000,000 USD revenue
threshold and may use the Licensed Work freely, even for Managed Services:

(a) Government Agencies: Government agencies and publicly-funded breeding
    programs at all levels (federal, state, local).
(b) CGIAR and International Programs: CGIAR centers and their affiliated
    programs, international agricultural research organizations.
(c) Non-Profit Organizations: Registered non-profit organizations and NGOs
    engaged in agricultural research, development, or humanitarian work.
(d) Farmer Cooperatives: Farmer cooperatives and farmer producer organizations,
    regardless of size or revenue.
(e) Individual Researchers: Individual researchers, faculty, and students at
    any educational institution for personal research projects, teaching, coursework,
    and thesis work. Individual use is always free.
(f) Educational Institutions: Educational institutions are subject to
    geographic tiers based on the World Bank income classification of the country
    where the institution is headquartered. See Section 3.2.1 for details.
(g) Developing Country Enterprises: For-Profit Agricultural Enterprises
    headquartered in countries classified as "Low Income" or "Lower-Middle Income"
    by the World Bank, provided Annual Revenue does not exceed $10,000,000 USD.

#### 3.2.1 GEOGRAPHIC TIERS FOR EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS

Institutional licensing fees for educational institutions are determined by the
World Bank income classification of the country where the institution is
headquartered. Individual researcher use remains free in all tiers.

TIER 1: LOW INCOME COUNTRIES
Status: Free
All educational and research institutions headquartered in countries classified
as "Low Income" by the World Bank may use the Licensed Work without any fees.
Anti-Abuse Provision: This exemption applies ONLY to institutions that are 
genuinely headquartered and primarily operate in the low-income country.

TIER 2: LOWER-MIDDLE INCOME COUNTRIES
Status: Free for first 3 years, then minimal fees
Institutions headquartered in "Lower-Middle Income" countries receive a 3-year
grace period. After Grace Period (Year 4+):
- Small institutions (annual agricultural research budget < $5,000,000 USD): Free
- Medium institutions (research budget $5M - $50M USD): $2,500 USD/year
- Large institutions (research budget > $50,000,000 USD): $5,000 USD/year

TIER 3: UPPER-MIDDLE INCOME COUNTRIES
Status: Free for first year, then moderate fees
Institutions headquartered in "Upper-Middle Income" countries receive a 1-year
grace period. After Grace Period (Year 2+):
- Small institutions (annual agricultural research budget < $10,000,000 USD): Free
- Medium institutions (research budget $10M - $50M USD): $5,000 USD/year
- Large institutions (research budget > $50,000,000 USD): $10,000 USD/year

TIER 4: HIGH INCOME COUNTRIES
Status: Standard fees (immediate for institutional use)
Institutions headquartered in "High Income" countries are subject to immediate
fees for institutional deployment. 
Institutional Use Fees:
- Small institutions (annual agricultural research budget < $10,000,000 USD): Free
- Medium institutions (research budget $10M - $100M USD): $10,000 - $25,000 USD/year
- Large institutions (research budget > $100,000,000 USD): $25,000 - $50,000 USD/year
- Elite institutions (endowment > $1,000,000,000 USD): $50,000 - $100,000 USD/year

#### 3.2.2 GRACE PERIOD MECHANICS

(a) Start Date: Grace period begins on the date of first institutional
    deployment. Individual researcher use does not trigger the grace period.
(b) Notification: Institutions must notify Licensor of first institutional
    deployment within 30 days to establish grace period start date.
(c) Transition Notice: At end of grace period, institutions receive 90-day
    advance notice before fees apply.
(d) Hardship Extension: Institutions may request grace period extension due to
    financial hardship, natural disasters, or other extraordinary circumstances.
(e) Verification: Institutions self-report their tier and research budget.
    Licensor may request verification for large institutions.

#### 3.2.3 ADDITIONAL PROVISIONS

(a) Hardship Waiver: Institutions facing extraordinary financial hardship may
    apply for fee waivers or reductions.
(b) Consortium Licensing: Multiple institutions may form consortia to share a
    single institutional license for a discount.
(c) Multi-Year Commitment Discount: 3-year commitment (20% discount), 5-year 
    commitment (30% discount).
(d) World Bank Classification Updates: If a country's World Bank income
    classification changes, institutions have 2 years to transition to the new tier.

#### 3.2.4 ANTI-ABUSE AND VERIFICATION

To prevent exploitation of geographic tiers:
- Institutions must have genuine physical presence and operations in the claimed country.
- Licensor may verify headquarters location, operations, and primary markets served.
- Institutions found to be misrepresenting their tier will be reclassified.

---

### 4. ETHICAL USE RESTRICTIONS

#### 4.1 PROHIBITED USES

ALL use of the Licensed Work, whether free or under a Commercial License,
is PROHIBITED in connection with:

(a) Genetic Use Restriction Technologies (GURTs): Any technology that
    restricts the use of genetic material, including but not limited to technologies
    that render seeds or plant genetic material sterile, non-viable, or dependent
    on proprietary chemical inducers.
(b) Terminator Technology: Any technology designed to produce sterile seeds
    or prevent farmers from saving, replanting, or sharing seeds.
(c) Seed Dependency Technology: Any technology that creates farmer
    dependency on proprietary chemicals.
(d) Seed Termination: Any method, technology, or practice designed to prevent
    seeds from being saved, replanted, shared, or used for subsequent generations.

Exemptions: This prohibition does not apply to:
(a) Chemically-inducible gene expression systems used solely for research
    purposes in controlled environments;
(b) Technologies where the activating chemical is publicly available and
    non-proprietary;
(c) Biocontainment systems designed primarily for environmental protection;
(d) Optional trait enhancement systems where base plant functionality
    remains intact and commercially viable without chemical application.

#### 4.2 AUTOMATIC TERMINATION FOR ETHICAL VIOLATIONS

Any use of the Licensed Work in violation of Section 4.1 results in IMMEDIATE
and AUTOMATIC termination of all license rights, including any Commercial
License, without notice and without opportunity to cure.

#### 4.3 CERTIFICATION

By using the Licensed Work, You certify that You will not use the Licensed Work 
in connection with any Prohibited Technology and will not transfer the Licensed 
Work to any party engaged in Prohibited Technology activities.

